\begin{align*} P(X=x) &= P(x-1 < X \leq x)\\ &= P(X\leq x) - P(X\leq x-1)\\ &= F(x) - F(x-1)\\ &= \left(1-\frac{1}{2^{x-1}}\right)-\left(1-\frac{1}{2^{x-2}}\right)\\ &= \frac{1}{2^{x-2}} - \frac{1}{2^{x-1}}\\ &= \frac{1}{2^{x-1}} \end{align*}
P(X\leq a) + P(a < X\leq b) = P(X\leq b)
F(a) + P(a<X\leq b) = F(b)
P(a< X\leq b) = F(b) - F(a).
